The paper deals with privacy and security concerns in mobile sensing applications, which are typically addressed in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also presents a novel autoencoder-based approach for data minimization and obfuscation, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis and experiments conducted to evaluate the proposed approach, which are typical of the data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
